<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-09-14T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-09-14T00:00:00-05:00" n="69" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d69">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">Roosevelt Papers</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Prime Minister <persName type="from">Churchill</persName> to President <persName type="to">Roosevelt</persName></hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Quebec</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-09-14">September 14, 1944</date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">My Dear Friend</hi>, I understand that we are
                            meeting at 11:30<note n="1" xml:id="d69fn1">See <hi rend="italic">post</hi>, <ref target="#pg_342">p. 342</ref>.</note> about
                                <gloss target="#t_StageII1">Stage 2</gloss>. Dick Law arrived here
                            late last night, and I wonder whether I might bring him at 11 o’clock
                            with or without Anthony,<note n="2" xml:id="d69fn2">Eden.</note> to
                            discuss the application of <gloss target="#t_UNRRA1">U.N.R.R.A.</gloss>
                            to Italy. He tells me that a compromise proposal would get through
                            whereby 50 million dollars of <gloss target="#t_UNRRA1">U.N.R.R.A.</gloss> would be available for Italy. I consider this
                            should be an essential part of our friendly gesture to Italy.</p>
                        <p>If agreeable then, I will turn up at 11.<note n="3" xml:id="d69fn3">No
                                record of the discussion at the 11 o’clock meeting between Roosevelt
                                and Churchill on September 14 has been found.</note></p>
                        <p>Yours always,</p>
                        <closer><signed>W[<hi rend="smallcaps">inston S.
                            Churchill</hi>]</signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>